        "text": "B–4 Suppose such a matrix A exists. If the eigenvalues of A (over the complex numbers) are distinct, then there exists a complex matrix C such that B = CAC−1 is diagonal. Consequently, sin B is diagonal. But then sinA = C−1 (sin B)C must be diagonalizable, a contra- diction. Hence the eigenvalues of A are the same, and A has a conjugate B = CAC−1 over the complex numbers of the form",
